<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Mixer service</p>
    <h2>Commercial mixer service for bakeries, pizzerias, restaurants, and institutional kitchens.</h2>

    <p>Commercial mixers are bakery and pizzeria workhorses. Bread programs, dough operations, batter preparation, and high-volume cake production all depend on planetary or spiral mixer reliability. Bowl-lift safety is OSHA-critical; pinch-point injuries on commercial mixers are well-documented OSHA citation cases. We service commercial mixers across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties.</p>

    <p><strong>Hobart Legacy series planetary mixers</strong> (ITW Food Equipment) dominate the US market: HL120 (12 quart), HL200 (20 quart), HL400 (40 quart), HL600 (60 quart), HL800 (80 quart), HL1400 (140 quart). The Legacy is the bulk of our mixer service volume across LA-area bakeries and pizzerias. <strong>Univex</strong> (independent) is common in pizzerias and mid-volume bakeries. <strong>Varimixer</strong> (Danish premium) is the spiral mixer of choice for artisan bakeries running high-hydration dough. <strong>KitchenAid Commercial</strong> (Whirlpool subsidiary, NSF-listed) covers the smaller-capacity countertop commercial segment.</p>

    <p>Service scope: bowl-lift safety interlocks (OSHA compliance, the most common service item), planetary drive motor service, bowl-lift motor service, gear transmission rebuild and oil seal replacement, contactor and capacitor service, on/off switch replacement. We treat bowl-lift safety as priority because the consequences of OSHA non-compliance are documented and severe.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 license. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/licensed/">License verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Failure modes</p>
    <h2>Typical commercial mixer failures, in order of frequency.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Bowl-lift safety interlock failure (OSHA-critical).</strong> Year 5 to 9 typical. Mixer must stop when bowl is lowered; failed interlock means mixer keeps running, OSHA citation territory. $260 to $440 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor capacitor or contactor.</strong> Common 6 to 10 year failure. Mixer won't start on cycle command. $200 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Bowl-lift motor (Hobart Legacy separate from drive motor).</strong> Year 8 to 12. Bowl won't lift, or lifts erratically. $580 to $880.</li>
      <li><strong>Gear transmission oil seal.</strong> Oil leak from gearbox; if caught early, seal replacement $440 to $720 plus oil refill. If ignored, gear teeth wear $1,400 to $2,400 rebuild.</li>
      <li><strong>Planetary drive motor.</strong> Year 12 to 15+ on heavy-use Hobart Legacy; longer on lower-use units. $880 to $1,400.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive belt (smaller models).</strong> Year 4 to 7. KitchenAid Commercial and smaller Univex models have belt drives. $180 to $320.</li>
      <li><strong>On/off switch.</strong> Year 8 to 12. $140 to $260.</li>
      <li><strong>Bowl scrapers and attachment wear.</strong> Routine maintenance; we identify worn parts during service.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Brand notes</p>
    <h2>What we see by brand on mixer service calls.</h2>

    <p><strong>Hobart Legacy (ITW Food Equipment).</strong> HL120, HL200, HL400, HL600, HL800, HL1400 by quart capacity. Cast-iron gear transmissions, separate bowl-lift motor on HL200 and larger. Hobart Legacy mixers from the 1990s are still in service in LA bakeries with periodic component replacement; the cabinet outlasts components by decades.</p>

    <p><strong>Univex (independent).</strong> Pizzerias and mid-volume bakeries. Less expensive than Hobart Legacy, simpler architecture, fully serviceable. Univex 12-quart, 20-quart, and 40-quart common.</p>

    <p><strong>Varimixer (Danish premium).</strong> Spiral mixers for artisan bakeries running high-hydration dough (sourdough, ciabatta, focaccia, panettone). Spiral mixers are different from planetary; the spiral hook descends into the bowl rather than orbiting around. Varimixer parts via Danish import distribution; 7 to 14 day ship on premium components.</p>

    <p><strong>KitchenAid Commercial (Whirlpool subsidiary).</strong> NSF-listed, smaller-capacity countertop commercial segment. KitchenAid Commercial is approved for NFL and NHL stadium concessions, hospital kitchens, school cafeterias. Different from residential KitchenAid stand mixer despite cosmetic similarity.</p>

    <p><strong>Globe (Edgecraft, independent).</strong> Mid-tier mixer alongside their slicer line. Common in mid-volume operations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bakery in Pasadena · Hobart Legacy HL400 (12 years)</h3>
        <p>Bowl-lift safety interlock flagged during health inspection plus gear transmission oil seep noted. Replaced safety interlock plus oil seal preventively (avoiding cascading damage). Total: $980. OSHA documentation provided to operator.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pizzeria in West Hollywood · Univex 40-quart (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Won't start. Diagnosed: motor contactor degraded. Replaced contactor plus tested through full duty cycle. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Artisan bakery in Beverly Hills · Varimixer SP30 spiral (10 years)</h3>
        <p>Spiral hook drive grinding noise. Diagnosed: gearbox oil seal failed; oil migrated into bearing housing. Caught at seal stage. Replaced oil seal, refilled gearbox with manufacturer-spec oil, tested through high-hydration dough cycle. Total: $720.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>School cafeteria in Long Beach · Hobart Legacy HL600 (15 years)</h3>
        <p>Bowl-lift motor failed. Replaced bowl-lift motor (separate from planetary drive motor on HL600). Tested through full lift cycle plus interlock verification. Total: $880.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hotel pastry kitchen in Calabasas · KitchenAid Commercial NSF (5 years)</h3>
        <p>Drive belt slipping under heavy bread-dough load. Replaced drive belt plus realigned drive sheave. Educated operator on dough-volume limits per the NSF spec. Total: $260.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for commercial mixers, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hobart Legacy series (HL120 through HL1400), Univex countertop and floor mixers, Varimixer spiral mixers, KitchenAid Commercial NSF, Globe mixers. Bowl-lift safety interlocks, planetary drive motors, bowl-lift motors, gear transmissions (oil seals plus rebuilds), contactors, capacitors, on/off switches, drive belts, attachment service.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> spiral mixer reverse-rotation conversion (specialty modification, not standard service); Hobart Legacy gear transmission complete replacement (we rebuild on-site if viable, refer to factory rebuild service if cabinet condition warrants); industrial dough-mixing systems for large-scale wholesale bakeries (specialty industrial trade with belt-driven multi-spindle architectures). New mixer installation we coordinate but don't perform.</p>
  </div>
</section>

